---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About the CIESIN Map Archive">
  <div class="container section">
    <h1 class="section-title">About the CIESIN Map Archive</h1>

    <div class="about-content">
      <p>
        The <strong>CIESIN Map Archive</strong> is a searchable digital archive of high-resolution maps
        authored and maintained by the <a href="https://www.ciesin.columbia.edu/">Center for International
        Earth Science Information Network (CIESIN)</a> at Columbia University.
      </p>

      <h2>STAC Specification</h2>
      <p>
        All maps in this archive are cataloged using the
        <a href="https://stacspec.org/">SpatioTemporal Asset Catalog (STAC)</a> specification,
        enabling interoperability with the broader geospatial data ecosystem. Each map is a
        STAC Item with standardized metadata including spatial extent, temporal coverage, and
        thematic classification.
      </p>

      <h2>Collections</h2>
      <p>
        Maps are organized into thematic collections (e.g., climate, population, land use)
        and can be browsed by country (admin0 level) or searched by keyword, location, and
        date range.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Access</h2>
      <p>
        Map images are served via Cloudflare's global network for fast access worldwide.
        The STAC metadata is available through both the web interface and a programmatic
        API for integration into data science workflows.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-content {
    max-width: 700px;
  }
  .about-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .about-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
